Truth is every time I try to finish my end of 2022 REEL I sob crying! Pure gratitude and happiness floods my heart and it gets me over the top emotional. If you know me u know I am very emotional and so I just needed to come on here and post my typical week to week post/motivation! Our last Freeman Butt Lift Session of the year! By the end of today I’ll have a whole 2022/2023 post like the rest of the world but timing… so here we are.
…
I promised myself I was not waiting until the new year to go attack my goals, to feel good again, to gain momentum and get back on my regimen. I finally hopped on the Inbody for the first time in quite some time 2 weeks ago and it told me I was back at 27% with some muscle loss…. It truly wasn’t about the number but rather how I felt at that those numbers and knowing the bad habits I picked back up. I also know what good feels to me I said absolutely not… this is the reality check that was needed and the on switch was hit! Ended my year back down to 25% and gained 1.3lbs of my muscle back in those two weeks… it wasn’t chasing these numbers at all but what I was Chasing was routine… My SELF CARE & True wellness routine. That FEEL good routine.. that I can give my husband a better wifey routine, my son a better more patient momma routine, my clients a no excuse coach mentality and encourage them in a way I do best because I am leading by example and doing it all myself! When I set these “number” goals it’s genuinely because how I feel when I’m there due to the healthy routine I am in to be there so I was proud to see that scan yesterday for sure but it was knowing the shifts I made and feeling good about those that I focused in on celebrating! 👊🏽💪 I hope this year you love yourself on the way to where you are going and you fall in love with the journey not wait to celebrate when you hit the finish line! The magic is within the journey and hard work you put in to get there… take time to show gratitude for those baby steps you take to the better version of you 💪❌⭕️🥰 @a_dfitness @dfree31 #AandDFitness #Family #Fun #Fitness #gratitude #Blessed #Grateful #Fit #Fitmom #hamstrings #Glutes #movement #workout #legday

We are up 3.8 lbs which I am happy with because we need to make sure this munchkin is healthy and growing of course but after the first trimester gaining unnecessary weight I’m happy to see the body fat has dropped 3.2% and the muscle has jumped up 4.4lbs. As much as I preach MINDSET when on your health and fitness journey it’s always still a battle and have to intentionally practice it all myself… especially when your body is just growing and the number is just rising. Daily I have to remind myself this beautiful strong body of mine is growing a human and things are going to look different for the time being, embrace it, appreciate it, and love on the journey as much as I can because it will be oh so worth it! I never give myself enough credit but since we hit the second trimester I have been so Much better. I am active daily from HIIT workouts to strength training plus adding 2.5 plus mile walks in 4-5 times a week…lately more on the lower side due to weather and appointments but WE MOVE and in an amazing way 6 times a week! I have been so mindful of my nutrition not calorie tracking but making sure I eat enough and from a micro nutrient standpoint we are getting so much more than typical from juices, fruits, veggies, and smoothies! Trying to stick to more whole foods than supplements but we are supplementing with all pregnancy approved goods still! Water intake is excellent and I should be feeling so much more proud on a daily basis than I do so today I scream loud and proud for me because I deserve all this joy and I am more than worthy of it🥰💪🏽🫶🏼🙏🏼
